description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a categorization that reflects the fundamental form of communication in which the content is expressed and the human sense through which it is intended to be perceived.
note[0]_en: Content type also reflects the number of spatial dimensions and the presence or absence of movement in which content expressed in the form of an image or images is intended to be perceived.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A categorization that reflects the fundamental form of communication in which the content is expressed and the human sense through which it is intended to be perceived.

ToolkitDefinition_en: A nomen that is an appellation of expression that consists of a code, number, or other string, usually independent of natural language and social naming conventions, used to identify an expression.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a family who contributes to an expression of a moving image work by designing and creating post-production visual effects.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who contributes to an expression of a moving image work by designing and creating post-production visual effects.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a family who contributes to an expression of a musical work by using electronic audio devices or computer software to generate sounds.
note[0]_en: The creation of a new musical work is excluded.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who contributes to an expression of a musical work by using electronic audio devices or computer software to generate sounds.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a family who contributes to an expression of a nonfiction moving image work by taking an active role as a participant.
note[0]_en: Appearance on screen to provide contextual or background information is excluded.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who contributes to an expression of a nonfiction moving image work by taking an active role as a participant.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a family who contributes to an expression of a stage work through the general management and supervision of a performance.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who contributes to an expression of a stage work through the general management and supervision of a performance.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a family who contributes to an expression of a work by rewriting a composition for a medium of performance different from that for which a work was originally intended.
note[0]_en: Contribution includes modification of a work for the same medium of performance, etc., that keeps the musical substance of the original composition essentially unchanged, and excludes substantial modification that results in the creation of a new musical work.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who contributes to an expression of a work by rewriting a composition for a medium of performance different from that for which a work was originally intended.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a family who contributes to an expression that is a performance.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a family who contributes to an expression that is a seamless mix of kinds of content.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who contributes to an expression that is a seamless mix of kinds of content.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a family who is a conductor who contributes to an expression by leading an instrumental performing group in a musical or dramatic presentation.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who is a conductor who contributes to an expression by leading an instrumental performing group in a musical or dramatic presentation.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a family who is a performer who contributes to an expression by acting as a cast member or player in a musical or dramatic presentation.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who is a performer who contributes to an expression by acting as a cast member or player in a musical or dramatic presentation.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a family who is a performer who contributes to an expression by appearing on screen to provide contextual or background information.
note[0]_en: Appearance in nonfiction moving image materials or in introductions to fiction moving image materials is included. Appearance on screen in a non-performing role is excluded.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who is a performer who contributes to an expression by appearing on screen to provide contextual or background information.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a family who is a performer who contributes to an expression by dancing in a musical or dramatic presentation.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who is a performer who contributes to an expression by dancing in a musical or dramatic presentation.

ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who is a performer who contributes to an expression by leading a program, often broadcast, that includes other performers.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a family who is a performer who contributes to an expression by leading a program, often broadcast, where topics are discussed, usually with participation of experts in fields related to the discussion.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who is a performer who contributes to an expression by leading a program, often broadcast, where topics are discussed, usually with participation of experts in fields related to the discussion.

ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who is a performer who contributes to an expression by manipulating, controlling, or directing puppets or marionettes in a moving image production or a musical or dramatic presentation or entertainment.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a family who is a performer who contributes to an expression by playing a musical instrument.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who is a performer who contributes to an expression by playing a musical instrument.

ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who is a performer who contributes to an expression by providing interpretation, analysis, or a discussion of the subject matter on a recording, film, or other audiovisual medium.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a family who is a performer who contributes to an expression by reading aloud or giving an account of an act, occurrence, or other event.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who is a performer who contributes to an expression by reading aloud or giving an account of an act, occurrence, or other event.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a family who is a performer who contributes to an expression by relaying a story with dramatic or theatrical interpretation.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who is a performer who contributes to an expression by relaying a story with dramatic or theatrical interpretation.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a family who is a performer who contributes to an expression by speaking words.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a family who is a performer who contributes to an expression by teaching or providing a demonstration.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a family who is a performer who contributes to an expression by using their voice, with or without instrumental accompaniment, to produce music.

ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who is a performer who contributes to an expression by using their voice, with or without instrumental accompaniment, to produce music.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a family who is a performer who contributes to an expression of a musical work by leading a performing group in a musical or dramatic presentation.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who is a performer who contributes to an expression of a musical work by leading a performing group in a musical or dramatic presentation.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a family who is an actor who contributes to an expression by providing the voice for characters in radio and audio productions and for animated characters in moving image works, as well as by providing voice-overs in radio and television commercials, dubbed expressions, etc.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who is an actor who contributes to an expression by providing the voice for characters in radio and audio productions and for animated characters in moving image works, as well as by providing voice-overs in radio and television commercials, dubbed resources, etc.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a family who is an audio engineer who contributes to the audio content of an expression by manipulating, mixing, and assembling the multiple tracks of a recording.
note[0]_en: Remixing activities that substantially change the nature and content of the original work, resulting in a new work, are excluded.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who is an audio engineer who contributes to the audio content of an expression by manipulating, mixing, and assembling the multiple tracks of a recording.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a family who is an audio engineer who contributes to the audio content of an expression by supervising the technical aspects of a recording session.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who is an audio engineer who contributes to the audio content of an expression by supervising the technical aspects of a recording session.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a family who contributes to an expression of a comic book, graphic novel, etc., by drawing the text and graphic sound effects.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who contributes to an expression of a comic book, graphic novel, etc., by drawing the text and graphic sound effects.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a family who is included in statement of an "X presents:" credit in a manifestation that embodies an expression and who is probably associated with production, finance, or distribution of an expression of a moving image work in some way.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who is included in statement of an "X presents:" credit in a manifestation that embodies an expression and who is probably associated with production, finance, or distribution of an expression of a moving image work in some way.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a family who is responsible for a realization of a work.
note[0]_en: A creator of expression includes a translator, arranger of music, performer, etc. A creator of a work that is realized by an expression is also a creator of expression.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who is responsible for a realization of a work.

ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who is responsible for assembling, arranging, and trimming film, video, or other moving image formats, including both visual and audio aspects.

ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who is responsible for recording the minutes of a meeting.

ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who is responsible for the general management and supervision of the process of adding new dialogue or other sounds to complete a soundtrack for an expression.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a family who contributes to an expression by giving apparent movement to inanimate objects or drawings.
note[0]_en: Creation of the drawings that are animated is excluded.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A family who contributes to an expression by giving apparent movement to inanimate objects or drawings.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a word or phrase that distinguishes an expression from another expression of the same work.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A word or phrase that distinguishes an expression from another expression of the same work.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to a categorization reflecting a hue of the visual content of an expression.
note[0]_en: Colour may be present in an expression with a content type of "cartographic image", "cartographic moving image", "cartographic three-dimensional form", "notated movement", "notated music", "performed movement", "still image", "text", "three-dimensional moving image", "three-dimensional form", or "two-dimensional moving image".
ToolkitDefinition_en: A categorization reflecting a hue of the visual content of an expression.

description[0]_en: Relates an expression to an expression that is modified to create a new expression of the same work.
ToolkitDefinition_en: An expression that is modified to create a new expression of the same work.

ToolkitDefinition_en: An expression that is a modification of another expression of the same work.

ToolkitDefinition_en: A work that is a metadata work for an expression.
